1. *Dozvolim* ti da ostaneš kod mene (I allow you to stay at my place).
2. On ne želi da mi *dozvoli* da idem na put (He doesn't want to allow me to go on a trip).
3. *Dozvoli* mi da ti pomognem (Allow me to help you).
4. *Dozvolite* mi da predstavim svoju ideju (Allow me to present my idea).
5. Neću ti *dozvoliti* da mi govoriš šta da radim (I won't allow you to tell me what to do).
6. Molim te da mi *dozvoliš* da objasnim (Please allow me to explain).
7. Ona neće *dozvoliti* da joj drugi određuju životni put (She won't allow others to determine her life path).
8. *Dozvoljen* je ulaz samo zaposlenima (Entry is only allowed for employees).
9. Svi smo *dozvolili* da nas vodi strah (We all allowed fear to lead us).
10. Ako mi *dozvoliš* da kažem svoje mišljenje, mislim da griješiš (If you allow me to share my opinion, I think you're wrong).

Note: In Serbian, the word "dozvolim" can have different forms depending on the tense and the person it refers to. In the examples above, different forms are used to demonstrate the versatility of the word.